# Sample: Tetrahedron
# Source: Public-domain Platonic solid definition from Paul Bourke, "Platonic Solids".
# Source URL: https://paulbourke.net/geometry/platonic/
# License: Public Domain source data; OBJ representation hand-authored for this project.
o Tetrahedron
v 1 1 1
v -1 -1 1
v -1 1 -1
v 1 -1 -1
vn 0.577350 0.577350 0.577350
vn -0.577350 -0.577350 0.577350
vn -0.577350 0.577350 -0.577350
vn 0.577350 -0.577350 -0.577350
f 1//1 2//2 3//3
f 1//1 4//4 2//2
f 1//1 3//3 4//4
f 2//2 4//4 3//3
